Governor Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State, on Thursday, sent a list of 18 commissioner-nominees to the state House of Assembly for confirmation. The Speaker, Olakunle Oluomo, read Abiodun’s letter containing the list of the nominees during plenary in Abeokuta on Thursday. Oluomo said the governor had written to seek for the confirmation of the nominees. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that some of the nominees were Afolabi Afuape, a former Commissioner for Sports in the state. Others included Oludotun Taiwo, Ganiyu Hamzat, Funmi Efuape, Kehinde Oluwadare, Jamiu Omoniyi, Toyin Taiwo, Tunji Akinosi, Ade Adesanya and Adeola Odedina. “In furtherance of our mission to build our future together, please find attached the list of nominees for the post of commissioners for your consideration. “Please accept the assurance of my highest regards,” Abiodun wrote.